# GitHub Linguist configuration.
#
# Nova is not yet in the upstream github/linguist database, so GitHub cannot
# render the literal label "Nova" — an unknown `linguist-language=Nova` is
# ignored and the repo shows as "Other". Until our upstream contribution lands
# (see linguist/ for the ready-to-submit kit), we use Nova's closest known
# relative — Rust — as an INTERIM highlighting/stats stand-in so the repo reads
# as source code instead of "Other". This is a temporary label, not a claim that
# Nova is Rust; Nova's syntax is deliberately Rust-like, so highlighting is close.
#
# To switch back to the honest "Other-until-upstream" behaviour, replace the two
# `linguist-language=Rust` lines below with `linguist-language=Nova`.
*.nova linguist-language=Rust linguist-detectable=true
selfhost/*.nova linguist-language=Rust

# Generated / vendored / non-source trees don't count toward the language stats.
nova/target/**        linguist-generated=true
nova/nova_modules/**  linguist-vendored=true
bench/**              linguist-vendored=true
*.lock                linguist-generated=true
